      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ONCE A DIVA (4) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.3 lengths (23.18) behind WHITE HOT DREAMS at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings six times from 10 attempts. Overdue and expected to feature again. WHITE HOT DREAMS (6) crossed over from out wide but caught the leaders turning before drawing clear to score (23.09) at this track in a Grade 6 over 400m. Has never been out of the placings from four starts out of this box. Capable of going well again. PROTEGE (1) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 6 lengths at this track (30.88). The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Great chance to atone. INVICTUS TOMMY (2) racing over this distance brings the best out in him.",
